EXT. TRANQUILITY BASE - LUNAR DAY

Brandt comes down the rise slow, hands visible, Lindqvist and Shen behind him. The ring of flags stands around them, colors hard in the sun. The tripod camera's red light burns.

Brandt stops ten meters out. Keys his radio.

BRANDT:
Switching to channel two. Let's talk privately, gentlemen.

The old man at the grill doesn't move. The one in the second chair, CRICKET, gray stubble behind the visor glass, keys the OPEN loop.

CRICKET:
We'll talk right here. Whole world's listening anyway.

INT. FRONTIER MISSION CONTROL - CONTINUOUS

The Flight Director looks at the loop status: OPEN. Every word going to Earth raw. Nobody moves to change it.

EXT. TRANQUILITY BASE - CONTINUOUS

Brandt looks back at his crew, then walks closer. He reads the crate lids left to right, the small flag with too many stars, the grill.

LINDQVIST:
(blurting)
Where did you even COME from?

CRICKET:
We came in the mail.

A beat.

BRANDT:
(formal, for the record)
This site is designated for retrieval under the Lunar Heritage Neutralization Accord. I am required to ask who you are and by what authority you interfere.

The old men look at each other. Cricket stands up out of his lawn chair, unhurried, and faces him.

CRICKET:
We're the backup crew. NASA never processed us out. We're still on the roster, son. This is our mission.

STITCH:
(from his chair, not getting up)
This here's our camp. Pack the fuck off.

INT. WHITE HOUSE, COUNSEL'S OFFICE - CONTINUOUS

Four LAWYERS around a speakerphone, laptops open. One of them has a personnel file on screen: DAWES, E. — ASTRONAUT (ACTIVE). A fifty-year column of quarterly entries: $0.00. $0.00. $0.00.

LAWYER #1:
Tell me this is a database error.

LAWYER #2:
It's been signed off every quarter since 1972, by career staff, under four statutes. And three months ago somebody reactivated the annuity — we did — which means this administration AFFIRMED the status—

LAWYER #1:
So they're not trespassers.

LAWYER #2:
They're federal personnel on their duty station. If that crew removes them on camera, the crew of a foreign-flagged mission will be laying hands on serving American officers, live, on the Fourth of July.

Silence around the speakerphone.

EXT. TRANQUILITY BASE - CONTINUOUS

Shen steps forward, past Brandt, toward the nearest flag in the ring.

All four old men come out of their chairs at once. Nobody signals. They stand between him and the colors.

Shen stops.

The one from the grill, GUNNY, tallest, spatula still in hand, looks down at him through the visor glass a long moment. Then points the spatula, once, back at the Harmony rover.

The open loop stays silent. No one moves.

BRANDT:
(on the loop, eyes on the old men)
Harmony copies. Control, Harmony requests instructions.

The old men sit back down, one at a time, Cricket last. Gunny goes back to the grill and flips what's on it.

CUT TO:
